location: Staten Island, NYC, Tri-state area, New York
postcontent: Selling a very nice condition HK USP Custom Combat Model, AE (2004) date code,  Variant 1(SA/DA with decocker + safety) in OD Green. This is not your run of the mill USP.  It has Novak sights, decal grips, two tone, and a Jetfunnel flared magwell extension from the factory.  The Jet funnel magwell is removable with one allen key screw to utilize standard USP magazines.  This comes with the 2 original HK 16Rd Clear Jet-funnel magazines plus one extra i purchased. These have a weighted base plate to expedite reloads from the factory.  I also have 2 HK 13Rd flush fit magazines, and 4 HK 10Rd magazines.   Just the extra magazines would run you $300+ .  The jet funnel magazines have been stored with the base plates removed as to not keep excess pressure on the springs, the other magazines were all stored intact and unloaded.  This package also includes and original Insight Technology m2 UTL (universal tactical light) that is specifically designed for this gun (temporary switch side does not work, but can be lightly pressed towards full-on side for same effect).  2 Holsters included in price, one Safariland drop leg 6004-932-122 ($160) LH for use WITH THE LIGHT ATTACHED, and a Blackhawk Serpa CQC Carbon Fiber RH holster for belt / paddle usage ($40).  The Novac front sight does rub on the upper portion of the inside of the holster due to its height, but i wanted something to keep it in at the range.  I have the box, all original paperwork, lock, NY shell casing still in the package.  This is one mean home defense gun, 17 rounds of .40 with damn good sights, a tactical light and good grips.  Nicely balanced, minimal recoil, comes back on target very quickly.   This is one smooth shooting piece.  Minimal wear on it, always properly cleaned and lubricated before and after shooting. Clearly if your a NYS Resident you CAN NOT own most of these magazines.  I will only sell them to a LEO with proper ID, sale through local FFL only. title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch SL-7, 308win(7.62Nato), 1-10rd mag
postcontent: The SL-7 rifles were developed by German company Heckler & Koch during early 1980s as a para-military weapons for training reservists and possibly arming police. The rifles calibers / ammunition used 308Win (7.62mm for SL-7) were based on hunting rifles from the same company, shares a roller-delayed blowback action and general layout, but featuring shorter barrels and military-type sights and furniture (sling swivels, steel buttplates etc). Due to high price and German gun laws limitations, overall production of SL-7 rifles was limited and now those weapons are collector's items.The HK SL-7 rifles use roller-delayed blowback action, similar to that used in HK G3 rifle. Chamber is fluted to assist extraction. The cocking handle is located on the right side of the receiver (as opposed to HK G3), and folds forward when not in use. Manual safety is located on the left side of the stock, above and in the front of the trigger. Feed is from proprietary detachable box magazines, holding 3 (flush-fit) or 10(extended) rounds. Stock is made of wood, with additional wooden handguard (ventilated on SL-7) and steel buttplate. Standard sights include hooded front post on the barrel and drum-type diopter sight(similar to that used on HK G3),with settings from 100 to 400 meters in 100-meter increments. Receiveris fitted with mounting points for proprietary HK scope mounts.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt XS 1911 LW commander
postcontent:
For sale is a Colt 1911 lightweight nickel/stainless commander. Made for less than a year this is the 04860xs model. This was Colts attempt to get into the custom market in 1998. Production ran for less than a year and Colt had a hard time keeping build costs down due to the custom nature of the build. In 1999 the model became the 04860xse. Different sights, grip safety and more cast parts to keep cost down. Mine is the earlier more desireable model. It is in excellent condition having spent much of its life in the original case. Comes with original case, 160 rounds of target ammo and 90 rounds of carry stuff. Also included are 3 Wilson Combat mags and the original Colt mag plus a JW Rourke strong side carry and a De Santis Yaqui slide holster. I am the original owner. You can't
Find these anymore. Asking $1200 for it all. All reasonable offers considered. Would consider trade for comparable AR.
